This paper deals with interference coordination in a multicell network, which is a topic related to network communication and information theory. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also proposes a scheduling scheme, which involves optimization and decision-making, making cs.IT (Information Theory) another likely category. The paper also deals with fairness criteria, which is related to system control and optimization, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) a possible category. The paper also provides numerical results, which involves data analysis and visualization, making cs.MM (Multimedia) a possible category. Finally, the paper proposes a pattern set construction algorithm, which involves algorithm design and analysis, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) a possible category.
